<seg id=1> Primary and Middle Shool Students in Typhoon-Afflicted Areas in Zhejiang Began to Go to School As Usual. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Hangzhou, 2nd, September, Xinhua News Agency(Shen Haixiong, Shen XIquan): The 17th typhoon has lead to serious loss in the educational institutions in the disaster areas in Zhejiang, the number of the school in which the schoolhouses, facilities have been destroyed amounts to 1500. </seg>
<seg id=3> After the active resistance againt the disaster and the all-out efforts to save themselves by the government and the people in the disaster area, at present, most of the primary and middle school  in the disaster area have their ordinary operation. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The educational instituions in Zhejiang province recently sent working groups seperatly to Wenzhou, Taizhou  etc,to direct the restoring of the education in those disaster areas. </seg>
<seg id=5> The Wenzhou municipal educational committee organized more than 20 office workers and divided them into 7 groups which would be sent to Leqing, Ouhai, Dongtou, Pingyan, etc. There, they would help renovate the campus and make preparations for the new term. 200,000 yuan has also been allocated for the educational disaster relief. </seg>
<seg id=6> The educational administrative institutions in every disaster-attacked cities and counties would reduce or remit the tuitions for those students who cannot afford the tuition because of the economical difficulties in the family caused by the disaster attack, or they will give some relief funds to them, ensuring that the students could go to school on time. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The leaders, teachers and staff in the disaster-attacked areas offer to go to work ahead of time. They tidy up the campus carefully by carrying on the sanitory sterilization, and repair the destroyed schoolhouses. </seg>
<seg id=8> Wenzhou municipal educational committee and Wenzhou municipal committee of the Chinese Communist Youth League united the teachers and students in the disaster-attacked schools and initiated a donation activity named "Showing Your Love to the Disaster-attacked Schools". Up to now, the city has received the donations from all walks of life amounting to more than 1 million yuan. </seg>
</p>
